brcdSysLogServerEntry.name: brcdSysLogServerEntry
brcdSysLogServerEntry.description: A row in the System Log Server table.

brcdSysLogServerAddrType.name: brcdSysLogServerAddrType
brcdSysLogServerAddrType.description: The syslog server address type. The supported address types are ipv4(1) and ipv6(2).

brcdSysLogServerUDPPort.name: brcdSysLogServerUDPPort
brcdSysLogServerUDPPort.description: UDP port number of syslog server.

brcdSysLogServerOutPkts.name: brcdSysLogServerOutPkts
brcdSysLogServerOutPkts.description: Number of sylog packets sent to this syslog server.

brcdSysLogServerRowStatus.name: brcdSysLogServerRowStatus
brcdSysLogServerRowStatus.description: Setting this object to createAndGo(4) results in addition of new row. Setting this object to destroy( 6)results in removal of a row. The value active(1) is returned for get and get-next requests. Other values in the enumeration are not used.
